data.text:
Roderick A. Maude-Roxby (born April 2, 1930) is a retired English actor who has appeared in numerous films such as The Aristocats where he voiced the main antagonist Edgar Balthazar (his only voice role), Unconditional Love, and Clint Eastwood's White Hunter Black Heart, playing Thompson.
